This paper deals with the design and evaluation of a novel routing algorithm for decentralized path-based transaction (PBT) networks. The paper discusses the efficiency and privacy concerns in existing PBT networks and proposes a new algorithm to address these issues. The paper's focus on network routing and privacy suggests that it is most likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. However, the paper also discusses security and cryptography concerns, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper's use of simulation studies and real-world data suggests that it could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's discussion of privacy concerns and the use of cryptographic techniques could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
